{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The elements that make up an L-system are modules, defined in Lindenmayer as structs that conform to the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create an L-system, you provide it with at least one module as a starting point, called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"axiom"},{"type":"text","text":", and one or more rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"An L-system maintains its state as a sequence of modules, and when you invoke "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"evolve"},{"type":"text","text":", the L-system iterates through all of the modules in it’s state, attempting to invoke one of the rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The set of rules within an L-system are evaluated, and the first one matching is used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If no rules match, then the module is ignored and left in it’s current place."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If a rule matches, then the L-system invokes its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"produce"},{"type":"text","text":" closure, and replaces the module with the set of modules that closure returns."}]},{"anchor":"Creating-your-First-L-System","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Creating your First L-System"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create an L-system, define the modules you require and call one of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"create"},{"type":"text","text":" initializers on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LSystem"},{"type":"text","text":", such as "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LSystem\/create(_:)-12ubu"},{"type":"text","text":", providing it with the module, or modules, that make up the starting set for your L-system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The following example illustrates defining two modules, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":", and providing an instance of one to start the L-system:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct A: Module {","    public var name = \"A\"","}","","struct B: Module {","    public var name = \"B\"","}","","var algae = Lsystem.create(A())"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The working logic of an L-system is captured in its rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rewrite"},{"type":"text","text":" function, which returns an new L-system after adding the rule you defined to its list of rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When you define a rule, provide it with the type of module that it should match and a closure that produces a list of modules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The following example adds a rule that matches to the module "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":", and replaces any instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":" with an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"type":"text","text":" followed by an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["algae = algae.rewrite(A.self) { _ in","    [a, b]","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A convenient way to define an L-system is chaining the rules one after another."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The full algae example, for example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let algae = LSystem.create(A())","    .rewrite(A.self) { _ in","        [A(), B()]","    }","    .rewrite(B.self) { _ in","        [A()]","    }"]},{"anchor":"Evolving-an-L-system","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Evolving an L-system"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"evolve"},{"type":"text","text":" on an L-system, it iterates through its state, applying the rules, and generates a new L-system with the updated state."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"evolved(iterations:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to repeatedly evolve the L-system."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read the state of an L-system through its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"state"},{"type":"text","text":" property, which returns an array of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The instances returned from the array are existential types (meaning they are some type that conforms to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":"), so expect to interact with them through the properties defined within the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, or by converting the type to an explicit type to access any additional properties your module’s type may include."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be aware that many L-systems extend the length of the state geometrically as they evolve, so calls to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"evolve"},{"type":"text","text":" may be quite expensive and take noticeable, or considerable, time and memory."}]},{"anchor":"Displaying-an-L-system","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Displaying an L-system"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two renderers are included with the Lindenmayer library, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/GraphicsContextRenderer"},{"type":"text","text":" for rendering into a SwiftUI "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/Canvas"},{"type":"text","text":" view, and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/SceneKitRenderer"},{"type":"text","text":" for generating a SceneKit "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/scenekit\/scnscene"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pass an instance of the L-system to a renderer, which reads through the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"state"},{"type":"text","text":" and generates a visual representation based on the relevant "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand"},{"type":"text","text":" that are associated with each Module."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation for either "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module\/render2D-1c1hi"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module\/render3D-2t57p"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand\/Ignore"},{"type":"text","text":", which renderers ignore."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/GraphicsContextRenderer"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"render2D"},{"type":"text","text":" property, and draws the representation by using the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand"},{"type":"text","text":" returned from the property as turtle graphics commands."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/SceneKitRenderer"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"render3D"},{"type":"text","text":" property, adding the 3D element and\/or updating the state of the renderer, to generate the SceneKit scene."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Lindenmayer comes with a number of built-in modules that you can use, either as a representation of your own modules as a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand"},{"type":"text","text":", or by including them in the set of modules returned by one of your rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Modules"},{"type":"text","text":" for the set of 2D and 3D built-in modules that the library includes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, the modules we created have no representation in either 2D or 3D, so the renderers can’t produce a visual display."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get a 3D display, extend the modules to provide a 3D rendering command from the property "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"render3D"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct A: Module {","    public var name = \"A\"","    public var render3D: ThreeDRenderCmd = RenderCommand.Cylinder(","        length: 10,","        radius: 1,","        color: ColorRepresentation(red: 1.0, green: 0.1, blue: 0.1, alpha: 1.0)","    )","}","","struct B: Module {","    public var name = \"B\"","    public var render3D: ThreeDRenderCmd = RenderCommand.Cylinder(","        length: 5,","        radius: 2,","        color: ColorRepresentation(red: 0.1, green: 1.0, blue: 0.1, alpha: 1.0)","    )","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The two segments are sized and colored differently to make them easy to distinguish for this example."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"With the modules, updated, you use the SceneKit renderer to generate a scene:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let renderer = SceneKitRenderer()","let scene = renderer.generateScene(lsystem: algae.evolved(4))"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The resulting scene, rendered in a SceneKit view:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"algae_4"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The sister library to Lindenmayer, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LindenmayerViews"},{"type":"text","text":", provides SwiftUI views that you can use to quickly display either 2D or 3D representations of the L-systems you create."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The source for this library is open source, and includes a number of example L-systems."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2D Example L-systems:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/fractalTree"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/kochCurve"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/sierpinskiTriangle"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/dragonCurve"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/barnsleyFern"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3D Example L-systems:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples3D\/algae3D"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples3D\/monopodialTree"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples3D\/sympodialTree"}]}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/creating_l-systems"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Creating_L-systems","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create systems that grow and evolve."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Creating L-systems","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Lindenmayer"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Lindenmayer systems","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RandomContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LindenmayerSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ModuleSet","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RNGWrapper","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ParametersWrapper"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples3D/algae3D":{"role":"symbol","title":"algae3D","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"algae3D"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer17ContextualLSystemV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An example of a L-system that produces a tree with monopodial structure."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples3D\/algae3D","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples3d\/algae3d"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/ModuleSet":{"role":"symbol","title":"ModuleSet","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModuleSet"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The set of modules found in sequence while processing the state of an L-system."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ModuleSet","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModuleSet"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/moduleset"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples2D/barnsleyFern":{"role":"symbol","title":"barnsleyFern","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"barnsleyFern"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer17ContextualLSystemV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An L-system that describes a fractal plant, also known as the Barnsley Fern."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/barnsleyFern","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples2d\/barnsleyfern"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples2D/fractalTree":{"role":"symbol","title":"fractalTree","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fractalTree"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer17ContextualLSystemV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An L-system that describes a fractal, or binary, tree."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/fractalTree","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples2d\/fractaltree"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem":{"role":"symbol","title":"ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A parameterized, stochastic Lindenmayer system."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/parameterizedrandomcontextuallsystem"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples3D/sympodialTree":{"role":"symbol","title":"sympodialTree","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"let"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sympodialTree"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer36ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystemV"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Examples3D","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer10Examples3DO"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SympodialDefn","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer10Examples3DO13SympodialDefnV"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PRNG","preciseIdentifier":"s:9Squirrel34PRNGV"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An example of a L-system that produces a tree with sympodial structure."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples3D\/sympodialTree","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples3d\/sympodialtree"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/GraphicsContextRenderer":{"role":"symbol","title":"GraphicsContextRenderer","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GraphicsContextRenderer"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A renderer that generates a 2D graphical representation of an L-system."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/GraphicsContextRenderer","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GraphicsContextRenderer"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/graphicscontextrenderer"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/RenderCommand":{"role":"symbol","title":"RenderCommand","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RenderCommand"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A collection of render commands, both 2D and 3D, built into Lindenmayer."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"RenderCommand"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/rendercommand"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples2D/dragonCurve":{"role":"symbol","title":"dragonCurve","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"dragonCurve"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer17ContextualLSystemV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An L-system that describes a fractal dragon curve."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/dragonCurve","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples2d\/dragoncurve"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/RenderCommand/Ignore":{"role":"symbol","title":"RenderCommand.Ignore","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Ignore"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A value that indicates the state of the drawing should ignore this module."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RenderCommand\/Ignore","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Ignore"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/rendercommand\/ignore"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Module/render2D-1c1hi":{"defaultImplementations":1,"role":"symbol","title":"render2D","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"render2D"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TwoDRenderCmd","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer13TwoDRenderCmdP"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of render commands to display the content in 2-dimensionals."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module\/render2D-1c1hi","kind":"symbol","required":true,"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/module\/render2d-1c1hi"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/Examples2D/sierpinskiTriangle":{"role":"symbol","title":"sierpinskiTriangle","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sierpinskiTriangle"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContextualLSystem","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer17ContextualLSystemV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An L-system that describes a fractal sierpinski triangle."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Examples2D\/sierpinskiTriangle","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/examples2d\/sierpinskitriangle"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/SceneKitRenderer":{"role":"symbol","title":"SceneKitRenderer","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SceneKitRenderer"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A renderer that generates a 3D graphical representation of an L-system using SceneKit."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/SceneKitRenderer","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SceneKitRenderer"}],"url":"\/documentation\/lindenmayer\/scenekitrenderer"},"doc://Lindenmayer/documentation/Lindenmayer/LSystem/create(_:)-12ubu":{"role":"symbol","title":"create(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"create"},{"kind":"text","text":"(["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Module","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Lindenmayer6ModuleP"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Co